WEBVTT

00:00.660 --> 00:03.713
[Crow caws]

00:04.320 --> 00:05.953
Frankie: <i>Out here in the middle,</i>

00:05.955 --> 00:07.621
<i>nothing gets us more excited</i>

00:07.623 --> 00:10.158
<i>than the grand opening of a new store.</i>

00:10.160 --> 00:11.993
Well, they did it.

00:11.995 --> 00:14.829
They outcheaped the Frugal Hoosier.

00:14.831 --> 00:16.831
Yesterday's Bounty?

00:16.833 --> 00:18.566
I'm telling you, Mike.
This is our new place.

00:18.568 --> 00:19.833
They've got everything...

00:19.835 --> 00:23.168
backed-over bread, preopened pasta.

00:23.170 --> 00:25.005
- Hmm.
- Generic Chinese cereal.

00:25.007 --> 00:28.309
Ooh! Look at this.
I got all this for 3 bucks.

00:30.779 --> 00:32.034
It's misshapen fruit.

00:32.058 --> 00:33.592
Looks like a tumor, but it's fruit.

00:33.746 --> 00:35.012
Their word, not mine.

00:35.014 --> 00:37.648
Brick: ♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

00:38.535 --> 00:39.984
I'm surprised to see you
in such a good mood.

00:40.719 --> 00:42.953
What, 'cause of Axl
not coming to Thanksgiving?

00:42.955 --> 00:45.489
Yeah, well, that
and the not talking to us

00:45.491 --> 00:46.824
or answering our calls for days.

00:46.826 --> 00:47.992
Yeah, I guess that.

00:47.994 --> 00:49.627
Look, it sucks. It definitely sucks.

00:49.629 --> 00:51.995
But I've just decided
I am gonna stay positive.

00:51.997 --> 00:53.930
I mean, he can't ignore us forever.

00:53.932 --> 00:56.433
Eventually, he's gonna need food
and clean underwear.

00:56.435 --> 00:59.373
He'll come home. We'll make up.
Everything will be fine.

00:59.375 --> 01:02.105
So, in the meantime,
I say we just stay calm

01:02.107 --> 01:04.373
and enjoy a bowl of Tiananmen Squares.

01:04.376 --> 01:05.474
[Chuckles]

01:05.477 --> 01:09.211
Oh! It's dishwashing detergent.

01:09.213 --> 01:10.813
No. Cereal.

01:10.815 --> 01:12.715
♪♪

01:12.717 --> 01:14.617
Both: So, where are you going
for Christmas break?

01:14.619 --> 01:15.618
You tell me first.

01:15.620 --> 01:16.519
Okay, we'll tell together.

01:16.521 --> 01:18.287
Ready? 1, 2, 3.

01:18.289 --> 01:19.622
- Paris.
- Nowhere.

01:19.624 --> 01:20.690
Oh!

01:20.692 --> 01:22.625
Give me your purse 'cause it's fabulous!

01:22.627 --> 01:24.026
Hey! No!

01:24.028 --> 01:25.061
[Groans]

01:25.063 --> 01:26.429
We don't know him!

01:26.431 --> 01:27.796
We don't know him!

01:27.798 --> 01:28.964
Yes, we do! Yes, we do!

01:28.966 --> 01:30.666
Lexie, stop! This is my friend, Brad.

01:30.668 --> 01:31.600
This is Brad!

01:31.602 --> 01:33.536
Oh, Brad, Lexie. Lexie, Brad.

01:33.538 --> 01:34.570
How's it going?

01:34.572 --> 01:36.172
Oh, my God. I'm so sorry!

01:36.174 --> 01:37.940
I've heard so much about you.

01:37.942 --> 01:40.642
Same. M-Minus the karate skills.

01:40.644 --> 01:43.378
Brad, this is crazy.
What are you doing here?

01:43.380 --> 01:44.746
Well, ever since I downloaded

01:44.748 --> 01:46.748
Lin-Manuel Miranda
as my new navigation voice,

01:46.750 --> 01:48.416
I've been dying to take a road trip,

01:48.418 --> 01:49.751
and who better to visit than you?

01:49.753 --> 01:51.286
Oh, I can't believe you're really here!

01:51.288 --> 01:52.621
[Gasps] Are you gonna stay
the whole weekend?

01:52.623 --> 01:54.089
You have to. I want to show you
the whole campus.

01:54.091 --> 01:56.724
Love to. Maybe we could start
with the ice machine.

01:56.726 --> 01:59.660
♪♪

01:59.662 --> 02:00.995
Hey, would you grab me a napkin

02:00.997 --> 02:02.697
and help me fill out
these insurance forms?

02:02.699 --> 02:04.031
Sure!

02:04.033 --> 02:06.101
By "grab you a napkin",
you mean get myself a beer,

02:06.103 --> 02:07.502
and by "fill out insurance forms,"

02:07.504 --> 02:09.204
you mean go watch TV.

02:09.205 --> 02:10.805
Hey, you know, Axl's not gonna remember

02:10.806 --> 02:12.240
to fill out the forms we sent him,

02:12.242 --> 02:13.641
and since he's not talking to us,

02:13.643 --> 02:14.909
we have no way to remind him.

02:14.911 --> 02:16.243
Brick: ♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

02:16.245 --> 02:17.712
[Sighs]

02:17.714 --> 02:19.981
Eh, don't worry about it.
I think he's on that.

02:19.983 --> 02:21.548
Well, how's that gonna play out?

02:21.550 --> 02:23.283
"Hey, Axl, you want to go out drinking?"

02:23.285 --> 02:24.551
"Uh, no, I'm just gonna stay home

02:24.553 --> 02:26.754
and fill out these insurance forms."

02:27.119 --> 02:28.388
He texted me.

02:28.390 --> 02:29.823
What?

02:29.825 --> 02:31.024
What do you mean he texted you?

02:31.026 --> 02:33.193
Yeah, he was working
on the forms the other day,

02:33.195 --> 02:35.295
and he asked if he
was allergic to penicillin.

02:35.297 --> 02:36.663
[Gasps]

02:36.665 --> 02:37.931
That cuts me like a knife.

02:37.933 --> 02:39.966
He really texted you a medical question

02:39.968 --> 02:41.067
instead of me?

02:41.069 --> 02:43.137
That is a shot across the bow.

02:43.139 --> 02:45.105
Okay. Wow. Message received.

02:45.107 --> 02:47.607
On the plus side, at least he
was filling out his own forms.

02:48.019 --> 02:50.576
Wait, you said
he texted you the other day.

02:50.578 --> 02:52.278
Why am I just finding out now?

02:52.280 --> 02:53.579
Frankie, it's not that big a deal.

02:53.581 --> 02:55.181
Then why wouldn't you
tell me he texted you?

02:55.183 --> 02:56.683
Why would you keep it a secret?

02:56.685 --> 02:59.052
Why wouldn't you tell me he
reached out to you and not me?

02:59.054 --> 03:01.320
- Huh? Why?
- Uh, 'cause of this?

03:01.322 --> 03:03.189
I'm sorry. I don't get why
I'm the bad guy.

03:03.191 --> 03:05.324
I mean, none of us like April.
We all said it.

03:05.326 --> 03:07.760
Mm, right, but you said it to him.

03:07.762 --> 03:09.529
[Sighs] Okay, yeah. I said it.

03:09.531 --> 03:11.397
But there's a whole list of things

03:11.399 --> 03:13.266
Axl said he doesn't like about me.

03:13.268 --> 03:15.901
I'm not kidding.
He literally made me a list.

03:15.903 --> 03:18.304
I'm sorry, but this is not okay!

03:18.306 --> 03:20.673
I mean, he's the one that
didn't show up at Thanksgiving.

03:20.675 --> 03:22.675
I should be mad at him, not him at me.

03:22.677 --> 03:23.709
Okay, that's it. You know what?

03:23.711 --> 03:25.610
I'm gonna write him an e-mail.

03:25.612 --> 03:27.980
You really need to send an e-mail?

03:27.982 --> 03:30.482
You sure this isn't something
frosting could solve?

03:30.484 --> 03:34.619
♪♪

03:34.621 --> 03:36.655
So... here it is.

03:36.657 --> 03:38.356
Wow.

03:38.358 --> 03:40.192
It's nice.

03:40.194 --> 03:42.093
Very bus-station chic.

03:42.095 --> 03:43.562
I know it's crappy.

03:43.564 --> 03:45.230
It's just temporary housing.

03:45.232 --> 03:47.232
It's like a holding bin for students

03:47.234 --> 03:48.600
until they find their forever room.

03:48.602 --> 03:51.102
Well, it's not the room,
it's the people in the room.

03:51.104 --> 03:53.171
Yeah, we don't really know
anyone in the room.

03:53.173 --> 03:55.272
You never know when someone's
gonna get "the call,"

03:55.274 --> 03:56.841
so we try not to get too attached.

03:56.843 --> 03:58.209
It's kind of the rules of the Bin.

03:58.211 --> 03:59.210
Mm.

03:59.212 --> 04:01.179
Okay, tell me everything.

04:01.181 --> 04:02.914
How is NYU? How's New York?

04:02.916 --> 04:04.615
NYU is awesome, and New York is amazing.

04:04.617 --> 04:06.918
You can get a hot pretzel
literally any time of the day.

04:06.920 --> 04:08.152
No.

04:08.154 --> 04:09.486
- Pick a time of the day, Sue.
- 2:00 a.m.

04:09.488 --> 04:10.654
- You can get a pretzel.
- Shut up!

04:10.656 --> 04:12.789
And New Yorkers don't say pop,
they say soda.

04:12.791 --> 04:14.958
And they don't say purse,
they say pocketbook!

04:14.960 --> 04:17.894
So I can buy a soda
with money from my pocketbook?

04:17.896 --> 04:20.063
- You'd fit right in.
- Ahh! Have you seen any celebrities?

04:20.065 --> 04:22.333
I'm pretty sure I saw
Greg Kinnear at a Starbucks.

04:22.335 --> 04:24.735
But I briefly blacked out.
When I came to, he was gone.

04:24.737 --> 04:25.736
- Oh.
- Oh, shut up, Brad.

04:25.738 --> 04:27.204
Here I am going on and on about myself

04:27.206 --> 04:28.839
and I haven't even asked
how you're doing.

04:28.841 --> 04:31.174
Actually, Brad, not so good.

04:31.176 --> 04:34.010
I'm living in a bin
and my family's falling apart.

04:34.012 --> 04:35.112
What?

04:35.114 --> 04:36.579
Wait, "Judge Joe Brown" falling apart

04:36.581 --> 04:38.681
or "Dr. Phil" falling apart?

04:38.683 --> 04:40.784
Axl's got this girlfriend
nobody likes and it all blew up

04:40.786 --> 04:42.318
and he didn't come home for Thanksgiving

04:42.320 --> 04:43.486
and my mom is devastated,

04:43.488 --> 04:44.587
and I'm not sure if I'm supposed

04:44.589 --> 04:46.789
to be talking to Axl
or not talking to Axl.

04:46.791 --> 04:50.092
It's all just very stressful.
There is so much drama.

04:50.094 --> 04:51.394
Sue, look at me.

04:51.396 --> 04:52.928
I am looking at you.

04:52.930 --> 04:54.330
I am here for you.

04:54.332 --> 04:56.332
And I'm gonna help you
forget all your troubles.

04:56.334 --> 04:57.933
With everything you've been through,

04:57.935 --> 04:59.268
you deserve to have some fun.

04:59.270 --> 05:01.270
They say New York
is the city that never sleeps,

05:01.272 --> 05:02.905
but tonight, that's gonna be Gumford.

05:02.907 --> 05:03.839
Really?

05:03.841 --> 05:05.207
Most stuff closes at 10:00,

05:05.209 --> 05:07.143
but the 24-hour mini-mart
closes at 11:00.

05:07.145 --> 05:09.011
[Gasps] Oh!

05:09.013 --> 05:10.746
- [Chuckles]
- Oh, yeah, yeah.

05:10.748 --> 05:11.747
Yeah!

05:11.749 --> 05:13.582
[ <i> Static</i> ]

05:13.584 --> 05:16.318
Okay, I wrote Axl an e-mail.
Listen to this.

05:16.320 --> 05:17.653
"How dare you?"

05:17.655 --> 05:18.887
Off to a great start.

05:18.889 --> 05:20.322
"Yes, things may have been said

05:20.324 --> 05:21.757
and feelings may have been hurt,

05:21.759 --> 05:23.325
but to not show up for Thanksgiving

05:23.327 --> 05:25.126
without so much as a phone call?

05:25.128 --> 05:26.328
I am outraged!

05:26.330 --> 05:27.829
Yes, that's right, outraged!

05:27.831 --> 05:29.731
So you listen here, you little punk..."

05:29.733 --> 05:31.365
Are you sure you're happy with the tone?

05:31.367 --> 05:32.733
Tone? What tone?

05:32.735 --> 05:34.969
"Listen, you little punk,
I've got two other kids,

05:34.971 --> 05:37.038
so if you think..."
Yeah, I'm hearing it now.

05:37.040 --> 05:38.406
I'm gonna tweak this.

05:38.408 --> 05:39.908
<i>So, over the next few days,</i>

05:39.910 --> 05:41.943
<i>I tried to find the right tone.</i>

05:41.945 --> 05:46.614
Axl, I am truly sorry for
the things I said about April,

05:46.616 --> 05:49.483
and I just want you to know
that I miss you every day.

05:49.485 --> 05:51.251
I can't stop thinking about...

05:51.253 --> 05:52.753
...what a jerk you're being.

05:52.755 --> 05:54.221
And to be perfectly honest,

05:54.223 --> 05:57.057
I'm not so sure I want
to be around such a...

05:57.059 --> 06:00.227
...sweet, loving boy
who lights up my life...

06:00.229 --> 06:01.629
...that I gave you,

06:01.631 --> 06:03.364
which you obviously don't appreciate.

06:03.366 --> 06:05.199
I guess you just don't care about that.

06:05.201 --> 06:06.633
But I can guarantee you this...

06:06.635 --> 06:08.836
you're gonna be so sad when I'm dead."

06:08.838 --> 06:11.104
- [Electricity crackles]
- [Sighs]

06:12.007 --> 06:12.906
[Sighs]

06:12.908 --> 06:15.742
Okay. I think I nailed it.

06:15.744 --> 06:17.311
"Dear Axl."

06:17.313 --> 06:18.245
Better.

06:18.750 --> 06:20.314
"When emotions run high,

06:20.316 --> 06:22.349
things can sometimes get out of hand,

06:22.351 --> 06:25.385
so I just wanted
to be clear and simple...

06:25.387 --> 06:28.321
I am not the only one
who hates your girlfriend.

06:28.323 --> 06:30.289
Your father hates her, Sue hates her,

06:30.291 --> 06:32.492
Brick hates her, we all hate her."

06:33.729 --> 06:36.128
But you do!

06:36.130 --> 06:38.070
This is so hard.

06:43.141 --> 06:44.307
- Shh!
- That was so much fun.

06:44.309 --> 06:45.976
I had no idea Gumford
had such great karaoke bars.

06:45.978 --> 06:47.377
Brad, that wasn't a karaoke bar.

06:47.379 --> 06:48.711
You just started singing.

06:48.713 --> 06:50.847
Hey, if you don't want it
to be a karaoke bar,

06:50.849 --> 06:51.881
don't play Katy Perry.

06:51.883 --> 06:53.416
[Both laugh]

06:53.418 --> 06:55.184
Hey!

06:55.186 --> 06:56.486
Lights out.

06:56.488 --> 06:59.547
There's no talking in the Bin
after midnight.

06:59.583 --> 07:00.382
Agh!

07:01.370 --> 07:04.404
And no personal effects
or decorations, either.

07:04.406 --> 07:06.039
We're not scraping tape off the bunks

07:06.041 --> 07:07.407
for a bunch of bin people.

07:11.780 --> 07:12.846
[Sighs]

07:12.848 --> 07:14.869
No, no, no. No more.

07:15.056 --> 07:16.723
You are not gonna live like this.

07:16.725 --> 07:18.691
Telling Sue Heck
not to decorate her room

07:18.693 --> 07:20.626
is like telling Michael Phelps
not to get wet.

07:20.628 --> 07:22.595
Sue, give me that picture.

07:22.597 --> 07:23.862
Are you gonna put it back up?

07:23.864 --> 07:25.864
Oh, we're gonna do more than that.

07:25.866 --> 07:27.666
Give me a glue stick.

07:30.137 --> 07:31.537
Regular or glitter?

07:31.539 --> 07:32.804
What do you think?

07:34.275 --> 07:36.041
Glitter. Okay, cool.

07:36.043 --> 07:39.144
♪♪

07:44.417 --> 07:46.351
Oh, my God. What happened?

07:46.353 --> 07:47.452
Oh, nothing.

07:47.454 --> 07:48.787
Sue and I just decided to give the room

07:48.789 --> 07:49.788
a little zhuzh.

07:49.790 --> 07:50.789
Brad's right.

07:50.791 --> 07:52.758
We may only be here temporarily,

07:52.760 --> 07:54.925
but we are still here!

07:54.927 --> 07:56.527
And there is no reason why we shouldn't

07:56.529 --> 07:57.703
get to know each other.

07:58.831 --> 08:00.309
My name is Sue.

08:01.464 --> 08:03.164
And I know you must have a name.

08:03.166 --> 08:05.432
You are not just
"Guy Who Farts in His sleep."

08:05.434 --> 08:06.949
I'm Scott.

08:07.670 --> 08:11.171
Everybody, "Guy Who Farts
in His Sleep" is Scott.

08:11.173 --> 08:12.372
Hey! Scott!

08:12.374 --> 08:14.841
And you are not
"Owns Too Many Turtlenecks."

08:14.843 --> 08:15.542
You are...

08:15.544 --> 08:17.223
Marcy.

08:17.946 --> 08:19.980
And you are not "Scary Quiet Guy."

08:19.982 --> 08:20.947
You are...

08:22.785 --> 08:24.184
Okay, we'll come back to you.

08:24.186 --> 08:27.253
Yeah! And stop calling us bin people!

08:27.255 --> 08:29.422
"Indian Harry Styles" is right!

08:29.424 --> 08:33.789
We may be bin people,
but we are people people first!

08:33.816 --> 08:35.150
Give it up for "Retainer Drooler!"

08:35.152 --> 08:36.317
She speaks the truth!

08:36.318 --> 08:38.153
[Cheering]

08:38.155 --> 08:41.188
[Robin Lewis Miller and Rouvaun Gus
Roman's "Let's Have Fun Tonight" plays]

08:41.191 --> 08:42.357
♪ Now let's have
a little bit of fun now ♪

08:42.381 --> 08:43.291
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

08:43.293 --> 08:45.192
♪ I make one check out of two now ♪

08:45.194 --> 08:46.561
- ♪ And it's a little bit... ♪
- [Music stops]

08:46.563 --> 08:47.762
You know the Bin rules.

08:47.764 --> 08:50.191
What the hell is going on in here?

08:51.568 --> 08:53.568
I'll tell you what's going on here, Dan.

08:53.570 --> 08:57.071
We are students
enjoying student activities

08:57.073 --> 09:02.167
at our university
which our parents pay for!

09:02.744 --> 09:04.078
- Yeah! Yeah!
- Yeah! Yeah!

09:04.080 --> 09:06.180
Yeah! We have rights.

09:06.182 --> 09:09.383
We may be temporarily housed
in temporary housing,

09:09.385 --> 09:12.453
but we are not temporary people!

09:12.455 --> 09:16.056
So I suggest you climb onboard
to the new Bin rules, Dan!

09:16.058 --> 09:19.225
Or the only thing not allowed
in the Bin is you!

09:24.066 --> 09:25.364
Whatever.

09:25.366 --> 09:28.201
I'm doing a semester abroad
next year, anyway.

09:29.471 --> 09:30.704
[Cheering]

09:30.706 --> 09:32.338
[Music resumes]

09:32.340 --> 09:33.639
- ♪ But everybody's talkin' about
the breakdown ♪ - [Laughs]

09:33.641 --> 09:36.242
Oh, thank you so much, Brad.

09:36.244 --> 09:38.244
This weekend has just been
the best ever,

09:38.246 --> 09:40.179
and you are amazing.

09:40.181 --> 09:41.814
Oh, I can't believe you have to leave.

09:41.816 --> 09:43.149
You never should have come here

09:43.151 --> 09:44.783
because now I know how much I miss you.

09:44.785 --> 09:47.853
You know, I only have
one class tomorrow.

09:47.855 --> 09:49.888
I guess maybe I could stay one more day?

09:49.890 --> 09:51.423
- ♪ Just smile if you're having
fun tonight ♪ - [Squeals]

09:51.425 --> 09:53.859
♪ Move your body nonstop,
take a breath ♪

09:53.861 --> 09:56.528
♪ And fill your glass up
and raise your hands up ♪

09:58.332 --> 10:00.866
Heh. Check it out. Potato snowman.

10:00.868 --> 10:02.635
[Chuckles]

10:02.637 --> 10:05.337
Oh, look! This one has legs.

10:05.339 --> 10:07.972
[Gasps] And it's anatomically correct.

10:07.974 --> 10:10.074
Put some shorts on that thing!

10:10.076 --> 10:12.511
[Gasps] Oh, you know
who would love this?

10:12.513 --> 10:13.612
Axl!

10:13.614 --> 10:14.746
I've been looking for the perfect way

10:14.748 --> 10:16.314
to break the ice, and this is it.

10:16.316 --> 10:18.116
I'm gonna text him a picture of it.

10:18.118 --> 10:19.384
He's gonna think it's hilarious.

10:19.386 --> 10:21.319
He won't be able to help himself.

10:21.321 --> 10:23.688
He'll text me back
with some funny comment.

10:23.690 --> 10:24.956
I'll reply with something witty.

10:24.958 --> 10:27.125
We'll both "LOL"
and smiley face each other,

10:27.127 --> 10:28.126
and before you know it,

10:28.128 --> 10:29.393
everything will be back to normal.

10:29.395 --> 10:30.561
[Sighs]

10:30.563 --> 10:32.429
You know, I was kind of mad at you

10:32.431 --> 10:33.698
when you couldn't help me
write the e-mail,

10:33.700 --> 10:35.432
but now I'm glad
you're completely useless.

10:35.434 --> 10:37.001
Glad to not be of service.

10:37.003 --> 10:39.170
- [Door opens]
- Brick: ♪You're gonna love our pizza ♪

10:39.172 --> 10:40.904
Hey, Mom. Do we have a hole punch?

10:40.906 --> 10:43.340
Brick, you've been singing
that commercial for days.

10:43.342 --> 10:46.009
Oh, crap. Is this some kind of new tick?

10:46.011 --> 10:47.578
♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

10:47.580 --> 10:48.945
Is what a new tick?

10:48.947 --> 10:51.482
♪♪

10:54.487 --> 10:56.853
So, who can tell me
what FDR said in response

10:56.855 --> 10:59.325
to the problems of The Great Depression?

10:59.992 --> 11:01.992
♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

11:01.994 --> 11:03.326
[Laughter]

11:03.328 --> 11:05.128
Think you're pretty funny, do you, Heck?

11:05.130 --> 11:06.997
♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

11:06.999 --> 11:08.331
No, I didn't get to finish.

11:08.333 --> 11:09.766
You know what else you're gonna love?

11:09.768 --> 11:11.234
You're gonna love
our principal's office.

11:16.311 --> 11:18.044
You didn't say
you were picking up a pizza.

11:18.046 --> 11:19.813
To be honest,
I don't even know why I got it.

11:19.815 --> 11:20.915
[Sighs]

11:20.917 --> 11:23.208
He still hasn't responded
to the dirty carrot, huh?

11:23.210 --> 11:25.384
No, and it's comedy gold.

11:25.386 --> 11:27.386
I mean, if carrot genitalia
won't fix this, Mike,

11:27.388 --> 11:28.588
I don't know what will.

11:28.590 --> 11:30.223
Felt like a winner to me.

11:30.225 --> 11:32.225
[Sighs] God, Mike.

11:32.227 --> 11:34.427
My son's not talking to me.

11:34.429 --> 11:36.729
I mean, really not talking to me.

11:36.731 --> 11:39.298
I can't pretend like this
is some little thing anymore.

11:39.300 --> 11:41.800
You know, you hear about these
families that are estranged,

11:41.802 --> 11:43.435
and you can't imagine
that happening to you,

11:43.437 --> 11:44.503
but it is.

11:44.505 --> 11:45.904
I mean, is this it?

11:45.906 --> 11:48.171
Do I not have a son anymore?

11:48.676 --> 11:49.942
♪♪

11:49.944 --> 11:51.777
[Sighs]

11:51.779 --> 11:52.945
[Knock on door]

11:56.383 --> 11:57.950
Hey. Got a minute?

11:57.952 --> 12:00.918
Uh... sure. Yeah.

12:02.623 --> 12:03.721
Huh.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.357
Still got the hole in the roof, huh?

12:05.359 --> 12:06.525
Yeah.

12:06.527 --> 12:09.794
It was nice in the summer.
Winter, not so much.

12:09.796 --> 12:11.229
So, listen.

12:11.231 --> 12:14.666
I know things got pretty crazy
before Thanksgiving,

12:14.668 --> 12:16.734
but it's water under the bridge, right?

12:16.736 --> 12:18.602
You know your mom. She is how she is.

12:18.604 --> 12:21.105
Sometimes she says things
in the heat of the moment,

12:21.107 --> 12:25.710
but anyway, she's pretty upset
about the whole thing and...

12:25.712 --> 12:27.011
I don't know if you got it or not,

12:27.013 --> 12:28.479
but she sent you a picture of a carrot.

12:28.481 --> 12:30.481
Yeah, I got it. It's hilarious.

12:31.030 --> 12:32.015
- Great.
- If you could take a minute,

12:32.017 --> 12:34.051
shoot her back a text
about the carrot, it'd be...

12:34.053 --> 12:35.219
Nope.

12:36.789 --> 12:37.854
What do you mean no?

12:37.856 --> 12:39.423
I mean I'm not talking to her.

12:39.425 --> 12:40.724
She went too far this time.

12:40.726 --> 12:42.493
You can say anything you want about me,

12:42.495 --> 12:44.861
but you start taking shots
at my lady, we got a problem.

12:44.863 --> 12:47.398
You know what I'm saying?
No one talks crap about my lady!

12:47.400 --> 12:49.365
I hear you, but your mom is <i> my</i> lady,

12:49.367 --> 12:51.101
and I need you to cut her some slack.

12:51.103 --> 12:52.602
She's sorry about what she said,

12:52.604 --> 12:54.971
and she extended the dirty
carrot as a peace offering.

12:54.973 --> 12:56.573
The least you can do is accept it.

12:56.575 --> 12:58.108
Why should I?

12:58.110 --> 13:00.744
Because to not make
an inappropriate comment

13:00.746 --> 13:03.313
about the dirty carrot will be
disrespectful to your mother.

13:03.315 --> 13:05.047
Oh, if you're gonna
give lessons on disrespect,

13:05.049 --> 13:06.616
maybe you should
talk to your wife first.

13:06.618 --> 13:08.368
She insulted the girl that I love,

13:08.370 --> 13:09.552
the girl that changed my life!

13:09.554 --> 13:11.321
- Okay, take it down a notch.
- No, you take it down a notch!

13:11.323 --> 13:12.589
There are two Axls now...

13:12.591 --> 13:14.524
one before April and one after April.

13:14.526 --> 13:16.459
- Is there a third one I can talk to?
- You just don't get it.

13:16.461 --> 13:18.994
Just 'cause you and Mom are dead
behind the eyes doesn't mean I am.

13:18.996 --> 13:21.330
The other night, April and I
talked until the sun rose.

13:21.332 --> 13:22.598
No, I get it. Your girlfriend's great.

13:22.600 --> 13:24.066
But you know what? So is your mom.

13:24.068 --> 13:25.334
So text her about the carrot.

13:25.336 --> 13:26.869
I'm not asking you, I'm telling you.

13:26.871 --> 13:28.137
Yeah, and I'm not 5 anymore.

13:28.139 --> 13:30.039
I'm not gonna do it
just 'cause you tell me to.

13:30.041 --> 13:31.807
Text your mom about the dirty carrot.

13:31.809 --> 13:33.375
Do you know what April would say

13:33.377 --> 13:35.143
if she found out Mom had the audacity

13:35.145 --> 13:36.478
to say she wasn't smart?

13:36.480 --> 13:38.380
First you'd have to tell her
what "audacity" meant.

13:38.382 --> 13:40.215
What is that supposed to mean?

13:40.217 --> 13:41.783
It means your mom is right!

13:41.785 --> 13:43.952
Your girlfriend's as dumb
as a bag of hammers!

13:43.954 --> 13:44.986
And we all think so!

13:44.988 --> 13:46.622
♪♪

13:46.624 --> 13:48.657
I'm out.

13:48.659 --> 13:50.125
He's not talking to me anymore.

13:50.127 --> 13:52.526
And I took Sue and Brick down with me.

13:54.231 --> 13:55.263
He's not talking to me anymore.

13:55.265 --> 13:56.330
Canadian Tire's all about fun.

13:57.009 --> 13:57.975
Hey.

13:57.977 --> 14:00.043
I hear one of my favorite students

14:00.045 --> 14:03.674
is having some trouble
in the disciplinary department.

14:04.001 --> 14:05.267
Hey, Dr. Fulton.

14:05.269 --> 14:06.635
Hey, Brick.

14:06.637 --> 14:08.403
Hey, let's talk.

14:11.441 --> 14:14.676
So, why did Mrs. Roberts
send you down here?

14:14.678 --> 14:16.544
♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

14:16.546 --> 14:19.113
Well, I said, "You're gonna love
our pizza", and she got mad.

14:19.115 --> 14:20.448
- But when I...
- I'm gonna stop you

14:20.450 --> 14:21.816
right there for just a second.

14:21.818 --> 14:23.084
Did you hear yourself

14:23.086 --> 14:25.820
when you say,
"You're gonna love our pizza"?

14:25.822 --> 14:27.588
♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

14:27.590 --> 14:28.656
Did I just do it?

14:28.658 --> 14:30.024
Yeah. Yeah.

14:30.026 --> 14:32.093
You know, Brick,
you're new to high school,

14:32.095 --> 14:34.295
and a lot of the teachers
might not be hip yet

14:34.297 --> 14:38.166
to your... you know, your quirks
and your eccentricities.

14:38.168 --> 14:40.301
You know, and that's no problemo.

14:40.303 --> 14:41.968
You know, I-I'm happy
to give them the 411.

14:41.970 --> 14:44.438
But it's just...
You know, but in the meantime,

14:44.440 --> 14:46.407
how... how are things going
in your world?

14:46.409 --> 14:47.874
♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

14:47.876 --> 14:49.510
- Uh-huh.
- Mm, fine.

14:49.512 --> 14:50.944
Things are going well with Cindy.

14:50.946 --> 14:54.014
Sue and Axl are back at college.
Mom complains about work.

14:54.016 --> 14:55.816
She and Axl aren't speaking
to each other.

14:55.818 --> 14:58.151
Oh, and I recently found
"To Kill a Mockingbird"

14:58.153 --> 14:59.319
in a hardcover.

14:59.321 --> 15:01.054
I'm gonna back you up
just a little, sport.

15:01.056 --> 15:02.122
Uh, that thing you just said

15:02.124 --> 15:03.389
about your mom
and... and your brother...

15:03.391 --> 15:05.591
that sounds like kind of a big thing.

15:05.593 --> 15:06.960
No, not really.

15:06.962 --> 15:09.029
Sometimes I hear her crying
through the walls.

15:09.624 --> 15:12.032
You know, I think what's happening

15:12.034 --> 15:14.134
is that this situation at home

15:14.136 --> 15:17.236
is manifesting itself
in this repetitive phrase.

15:17.238 --> 15:18.705
♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

15:18.707 --> 15:19.706
What repetitive phrase?

15:19.708 --> 15:21.641
[Sighs]

15:21.643 --> 15:23.409
You know, Brick,

15:23.411 --> 15:26.813
all stress has certain trigger points.

15:26.815 --> 15:28.548
For me, it was finding out that Shelly

15:28.550 --> 15:30.916
was having a baby with her
butt-faced, ponytail husband.

15:30.918 --> 15:32.251
But the good news is,

15:32.253 --> 15:34.887
we... we all find ways to cope
and move on.

15:34.889 --> 15:37.256
For example, I'm...
I'm seeing this great new gal.

15:37.258 --> 15:39.358
Her name is Barbara,
but I call her Shelly.

15:39.360 --> 15:42.461
She's 68 years old,
but she's very youthful.

15:42.463 --> 15:43.695
Anywho,

15:43.697 --> 15:46.031
I think you need to find a way
to relieve some stress,

15:46.033 --> 15:48.400
you know, blow off some steam,
you know, have some fun.

15:48.402 --> 15:49.197
Hmm.

15:49.222 --> 15:51.269
That's why I always say
yes to mall-walking

15:51.271 --> 15:53.605
with Barbara-Shelly.

15:53.607 --> 15:55.574
She sets quite a brisk pace.

15:55.576 --> 15:56.675
[Both chuckle]

15:56.677 --> 15:58.109
You know, she's younger
than Mick Jagger.

15:58.111 --> 15:59.644
Who?

15:59.646 --> 16:01.980
♪♪

16:01.982 --> 16:03.548
<i>The amazing thing about best friends</i>

16:03.550 --> 16:06.217
<i>is that they just seem to know
when you need them.</i>

16:06.219 --> 16:08.152
<i>They show up at the perfect time,</i>

16:08.154 --> 16:10.121
<i>and then, just like that, they're gone.</i>

16:10.123 --> 16:12.723
[Gasps] Brad. What are you doing here?

16:12.725 --> 16:14.725
I was just being wistful about you.

16:14.727 --> 16:16.761
This just in... I decided
to stay one more day.

16:16.763 --> 16:18.696
Really? Are you sure?

16:18.698 --> 16:20.265
I mean... I mean, it's great
that you can stay,

16:20.267 --> 16:21.932
but you've already been here three days.

16:21.934 --> 16:23.401
Don't you need to go to class?

16:23.403 --> 16:24.902
Nothing's more important than my bestie.

16:24.904 --> 16:27.104
Plus tonight, I was thinking
we could have fondue party.

16:27.106 --> 16:29.273
But I don't even own a fondue pot.

16:29.275 --> 16:30.307
That's okay. I've got one in my car.

16:30.309 --> 16:31.776
Wait, Brad.

16:31.778 --> 16:33.110
You were only gonna be here
for the weekend.

16:33.112 --> 16:34.945
Why do you have
a fondue pot in your car?

16:34.947 --> 16:36.313
Uh, I think a better question is,

16:36.315 --> 16:38.081
"Why wouldn't I have
a fondue pot in my car?"

16:38.083 --> 16:40.284
And an even better question is,
"Why am I such a failure?"

16:40.286 --> 16:42.119
Sue, I dropped out of NYU! This
whole weekend's been a big lie!

16:42.121 --> 16:45.355
Except for the part about me always
traveling with a fondue pot.

16:45.357 --> 16:46.523
Wait. Wait, wait, wait, what?

16:46.525 --> 16:47.824
You dropped out?

16:47.826 --> 16:49.592
Yes, everything I own is in my car,

16:49.594 --> 16:51.628
and I haven't even told my parents yet.

16:51.630 --> 16:54.130
What? I don't get it.
NYU was your dream school.

16:54.132 --> 16:55.698
More like nightmare.

16:55.700 --> 16:57.700
Everyone there is so dark and intense.

16:57.702 --> 16:59.903
I just had such a different upbringing,

16:59.905 --> 17:01.805
a whole different training.

17:01.807 --> 17:03.506
"I coulda had class.

17:03.508 --> 17:05.974
I coulda been a contender.
I coulda been somebody!"

17:05.977 --> 17:07.444
Bigger?

17:07.445 --> 17:10.378
"I coulda been a contender!
I coulda been somebody!"

17:10.381 --> 17:11.847
Bigger!

17:11.848 --> 17:14.349
"I coulda been a contender!
I coulda been somebody!"

17:14.352 --> 17:15.818
I could say bigger,

17:15.819 --> 17:17.819
but I don't know if I could handle it!

17:17.821 --> 17:19.521
[Applause]

17:19.522 --> 17:21.223
I've always been the star.

17:21.224 --> 17:22.925
I got Snoopy as a freshman

17:22.926 --> 17:24.660
when we did "You're a Good Man,
Charlie Brown."

17:24.662 --> 17:27.329
At Dollywood, I quickly went
from Cowboy #3

17:27.330 --> 17:29.130
- to Cowboy #2.
- Yeah!

17:29.132 --> 17:30.666
I mean, my ascent has been meteoric.

17:30.668 --> 17:32.801
But it was different at NYU.

17:32.803 --> 17:35.971
"I coulda been a contender.
I coulda been somebody!"

17:35.973 --> 17:37.005
Smaller.

17:38.809 --> 17:41.309
"I coulda been a contender.
I coulda been somebody."

17:41.311 --> 17:42.911
Smaller.

17:44.814 --> 17:47.349
"I coulda been a contender.
I coulda been somebody."

17:50.153 --> 17:52.020
I just don't fit in at all.

17:52.022 --> 17:53.221
Brad.

17:53.223 --> 17:55.156
You don't always love school right away.

17:55.158 --> 17:56.891
But you got to hang in there!

17:56.893 --> 17:58.626
I actually have a ton of posters

17:58.628 --> 18:00.027
that speak to exactly
what you're talking to,

18:00.029 --> 18:01.161
but they're all in storage.

18:01.163 --> 18:03.297
The point is,
the same thing happened to me

18:03.299 --> 18:04.999
when I first got to Gumford.

18:05.001 --> 18:06.400
But I don't like New York.

18:06.402 --> 18:07.702
Everything costs a zillion dollars.

18:07.704 --> 18:09.169
People are rude and pushy.

18:09.171 --> 18:11.438
I saw a guy once poop on the street.

18:11.440 --> 18:12.540
He didn't even try and hide it.

18:12.542 --> 18:14.609
He just looked at me like it was normal.

18:14.611 --> 18:15.643
I'm telling you, Sue,

18:15.645 --> 18:17.411
New York is nothing like "On The Town."

18:17.413 --> 18:18.778
I mean, the Bronx is up
and the Battery's down,

18:18.780 --> 18:19.779
but that's it.

18:19.781 --> 18:21.081
[Sighs] Wow.

18:21.083 --> 18:22.616
So what are you gonna do?

18:22.618 --> 18:23.650
I don't know.

18:23.652 --> 18:24.851
I guess I'll just listen to my dad

18:24.853 --> 18:26.253
and become a cop
or a construction worker.

18:26.255 --> 18:27.287
I've already got the outfits.

18:27.289 --> 18:29.823
Brad! Don't talk like that.

18:29.825 --> 18:34.594
You are one of the most amazing
and talented people I know.

18:34.596 --> 18:37.898
And, yes, you may not be deep or dark,

18:37.900 --> 18:40.501
but the world
already has enough darkness.

18:40.503 --> 18:44.538
So maybe you're not cut out
for the really heavy roles,

18:44.540 --> 18:48.610
but nobody will ever play
a better Snoopy than you.

18:48.612 --> 18:51.911
Nobody wants to see
Sir Ian McKellen play Snoopy.

18:51.913 --> 18:53.913
You are Snoopy!

18:53.915 --> 18:56.174
And the world needs Snoopy
more than ever.

18:57.236 --> 18:58.751
Brad, look at me.

18:58.753 --> 19:00.076
I am looking at you.

19:00.455 --> 19:03.289
It's not you
that wasn't ready for New York.

19:03.291 --> 19:06.058
It's New York that wasn't ready for you.

19:06.060 --> 19:07.192
You really think so?

19:07.194 --> 19:08.226
Oh, I know so.

19:08.228 --> 19:10.228
And you want to know what else I know?

19:10.230 --> 19:13.249
East Indy has a pretty amazing
theater department.

19:13.251 --> 19:15.333
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

19:15.335 --> 19:18.270
And ever since
a friend of mine came to visit,

19:18.272 --> 19:21.607
temporary housing is super fun.

19:21.609 --> 19:22.907
[Chuckles]

19:22.909 --> 19:25.577
♪♪

19:28.682 --> 19:31.583
Well [Sighs] got our statement
from the insurance company.

19:31.585 --> 19:33.618
The premium's higher than ever,
so apparently

19:33.620 --> 19:35.887
Life Mutual still thinks
Axl is part of our family.

19:35.889 --> 19:37.189
Really?

19:37.191 --> 19:39.156
Did Life Mutual say
he filled out the forms okay?

19:39.158 --> 19:40.758
Did Life Mutual mention how he's doing

19:40.760 --> 19:42.026
or if he misses us?

19:42.028 --> 19:44.195
I did not ask Life Mutual
any of those questions.

19:44.197 --> 19:46.097
[Sighs]

19:46.099 --> 19:47.498
Hey.

19:47.500 --> 19:49.333
It's okay. You're a great mom.

19:49.335 --> 19:50.768
He's gonna come home.

19:50.770 --> 19:52.604
He has to. His nunchucks are here.

19:52.606 --> 19:54.739
You think? 'Cause the waiting sucks.

19:54.741 --> 19:57.074
I miss him. Oh.

19:58.677 --> 20:00.010
[Spits]

20:00.012 --> 20:02.512
It actually tastes worse than it looks.

20:02.514 --> 20:03.946
♪ You're gonna love our pizza ♪

20:03.948 --> 20:05.348
Yeah, well, beside the pizza,

20:05.350 --> 20:06.849
you still love me, right, Brick?

20:06.851 --> 20:07.950
Well, I thought so,

20:07.952 --> 20:09.852
but Dr. Fulton said I'm being torn apart

20:09.854 --> 20:10.987
by our family situation.

20:10.989 --> 20:12.489
Awesome.

20:12.491 --> 20:14.023
He told me if I want to
relieve my stress,

20:14.025 --> 20:15.458
I'm supposed to have more fun.

20:15.460 --> 20:16.692
[Sniffs]

20:16.694 --> 20:18.094
You're at the wrong house for that.

20:18.096 --> 20:19.161
Now, hold on.

20:20.364 --> 20:22.496
He might have a point.

20:23.167 --> 20:25.134
<i>Sometimes life gives you lemons...</i>

20:25.136 --> 20:26.602
Mike: 1, 2, 3.

20:26.604 --> 20:29.672
<i>...and sometimes it gives you
freaky-looking lemons.</i>

20:29.674 --> 20:32.574
<i>It's what you do with them
that makes a difference.</i>

20:32.576 --> 20:34.843
[Laughter]

20:34.845 --> 20:36.278
- Oh!
- Ooh!

20:36.280 --> 20:37.579
Right up the middle!

20:37.581 --> 20:38.447
[Laughter]

20:38.449 --> 20:40.048
Yay!

20:40.050 --> 20:41.950
Oh! Oh!

20:41.952 --> 20:43.852
Whoo-hoo!

20:46.089 --> 20:48.390
Oh! Whoo!

20:48.392 --> 20:49.424
[Laughs]

20:49.426 --> 20:50.925
Whoo!

20:52.929 --> 20:54.863
Whoo! Whoo!

20:54.865 --> 20:57.532
<i>And that day,
we smashed the crap out of it.</i>

20:57.534 --> 21:00.535
<i>And we had fun.</i>

21:00.537 --> 21:02.403
Whoo!

